The Lady Of Burma - An Exhibition Honoring Aung San Suu Kyi
Dustin Moskovitz was invited
Come and Experience The Voice of Hope… One of a kind, Inspiring and Revealing Aung San Suu Kyi Timeline (1945-2010), astounding and rare portraits of ASSK by various artists, humorous cartoons about ASSK, and various presentations along with Skillful and Thrilling performances by New York’s own artists and much more… Special guest - Alan Clements (Author, Activist, Satirist, former Buddhist monk, and co-author of The Voice of Hope with Aung San Suu Kyi ) Experience and Inspire The Voice of Hope and explore: Who really is Aung San Suu Kyi? What is The current status of Burma and Aung San Suu Kyi? What is The Guiding Wisdom of her Revolution of the Spirit? What is The Nature of Freedom in an Interrelated World? Why we Should Care about Burma and Aung San Suu Kyi? This event is Free and open to the public. Refreshments & Burmese appetizers will be served. Please visit www.Burma-Network.com for more details and upcoming tentative program.
Saturday, July 17, 2010, 1 PM - 6 PM in PDT
Community Gallery [30 E. 35th Street, NYC - btw Park and Madison Ave],30 E. 35th Street,New York,New York,United States

Killer mac'n'cheese! __________________________________________________ ::::About:::: Afterglow was conceived as a chance to wind down after a long weekend by listening to some chill music and having a few drinks and maybe some dinner with friends. Tutu Tuesday featuring Naveen G and Atish
Dustin went
Burning Man is less than a month away, and since that epic desert experiment is the very inspiration for Tutu Tuesday, this is the best time of the year to get excited about tutu merriment! listed artist NAVEEN G kicked off this prized experience 2 years ago so it is with fitting pleasure that we welcome him back for another round. Resident ATISH and Naveen have a great musical chemistry so we will enjoy a tagging set between them--a masterpiece in the making. Our resident painter Tracy Piper cannot be with us this month but there will be no shortage of visual inspiration when NINA MEHTA joins the tutu crew as our in-house visual artist. The playa Tutu Tuesday is so worth getting psyched about so if you haven't got a tutu yet, this is your best opportunity to get one before the burn. $10 or $2 in a tutu before 11pm *handmade tutus for sale*
Tuesday, August 13, 2013 at 9:00pm - Wednesday, August 14, 2013 at 2:00am in PDT

Tutu Tuesday @ Short Stack (7:15 & B)
Dustin went
Holy guacamole, mister funky face! We are back at it once again. The delightful denizens of Short Stack (7:15 & B) once again invite you to our stupidly silly, lavishly lurid, stylishly sexy, terrifically torrid Tuesday afternoon affair. Hrm, whazzat? IT'S TUTU TUESDAY, BITCHES. A dance affair with the utmost flair. Do it up. Do it up riiiiii-ght. Strap a tutu around that waist and make haste, to 7:15 & B we say! From 2pm onwards (or Tu O'Clock, if you please), we'll be bumpin' and grindin' our way through the desert afternoon with the bounciest of beats. Puttin' some romp in that rump! Got no tutu? MAKE ONE! Too lazy? WE MADE ONE FOR YOU! Come early to snag one that's snug. Oh, did we mention our campmates Om Skillet will be serving delicious gourmet grilled cheese sandwiches?? JUST MENTIONED IT. Show up early and eat one. Even if you're lactose intolerant, you'll only regret it a little. They're that good. WHO IS GONNA PLAY ALL THE SASSY SEXY HOUSE MUSIC THAT WILL SURELY BE REQUIRED TO MAKE THIS PROPER? Glad you asked. This year round, we've plucked our musical pickings from three fine nations. Kit Seymour - our newest UK import, fresh off the airboat from London Roddy "The Ride" Lindsay - SF Mightykat - Montreal native, Short Stack regular Atish + Slee - SF Alex Blackstock - SF You know you wanna. So brang it, hot stuff. Sissy that walk over to 7:15 & B. Tuesday. 2pm 'til the sun goes down. Be there.
